headlines.description: Tre'Shaun Fletcher had 23 points, nine rebounds and five assists, Jaelan Sanford added 18, seven, and five, and Toledo beat Akron 55-36 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fletcher, Sanford lead Toledo past Akron 77-56

headlines.description: Nate Grimes had a career-high 20 points to go with 12 rebounds as Fresno State thundered past Wyoming 80-62 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grimes has 20 points, 12 boards as Fresno St. runs past Wyo.

headlines.description: Kellan Grady scored 23 points on 10 of 16 shooting, leading four into double-figure scoring and Davidson walloped George Washington 87-58 on Saturday, winning seven of its last nine.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grady leads Davidson past George Washington 87-58

headlines.description: Holland Woods scored a career-high 29 points on a school record 10-for-10 shooting and Portland State lead from wire-to-wire for a 94-81 win over Eastern Washington on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Woods scores 29, Portland State tops Eastern Washington

headlines.description: Jacob Grandison scored a career-high 21 points and Holy Cross rolled to a 73-57 victory over Loyola (Maryland) on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grandison leads Holy Cross over Loyola (Maryland) 73-57

headlines.description: Davaris McGowens scored 21 points, Kameron Langley had 17 with seven assists, and North Carolina A&T beat Hampton 92-84 on Saturday for its seventh win in eight games.
headlines.shortLinkText: NC A&T beats Hampton 92-84 behind McGowens' 21 points

headlines.description: Otis Livingston II scored 22 points and made four straight free throws in the last 7.7 seconds as George Mason held off Richmond 79-75 on Saturday in an upset that knocked the Spiders out of a tie for second place in the Atlantic 10 Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Livingston FTs help George Mason upset Richmond 79-75

headlines.description: Johnny Hamilton celebrated his birthday by scoring 20 points while grabbing 13 rebounds as UT Arlington held off Coastal Carolina 87-80 to even its Sun Belt Conference record on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hamilton has 5th double double, UT Arlington wins 87-80

headlines.description: Roosevelt Smart had 28 points and DJ Draper scored 10 of his 12 points in the final five minutes to help North Texas rally for a 74-70 win over Rice on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smart scores 28, North Texas rallies for 74-70 win over Rice

headlines.description: Jason Dunne scored 20 points, J.R. Lynch 19, including five of six free throws in the final minute and Hartford held off a surging Stony Brook 73-64 Saturday night, winning a third straight.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dunne, Lynch help Hartford hold on, 73-64 at Stony Brook

headlines.description: Deven Simms had 24 points to help Arkansas State hold off Georgia Southern for a 91-89 win in Sun Belt Conference action on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arkansas State hangs on to beat Ga. Southern 91-89

headlines.description: Jarkel Joiner scored 21 points on 8-for-13 shooting, Damiyne Durham added 16 more and Cal State Bakersfield cruised to an 81-58 win over Missouri-Kansas City on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cal State Bakersfield cruises to 81-58 win over UMKC

headlines.description: Richaud Gittens made a pair of free throws with 16 seconds left to give Seattle a 55-54 victory over Utah Valley on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gittens' late FTs lift Seattle past Utah Valley 55-54

headlines.description: Frankie Ferrari had 19 points and Jordan Ratinho scored 17 to help San Francisco beat Santa Clara 70-59 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ferrari, Ratinho lead San Francisco past Santa Clara, 70-59

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "Im getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. Its a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how Im going to dictate how my team wins.  Its a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... Its a process. Right now, its tough."
